& =\pi \int_{\frac{\pi}{6}}^{\frac{\pi}{3}}(1-\cos 2 t) \mathrm{d} t=\frac{\pi^2}{6}-\int_{\frac{\pi}{6}}^{\frac{\pi}{3}} \cos 2 t \mathrm{~d} t=\frac{\pi^2}{6}-\left.\frac{1}{2} \sin 2 t\right|_{\frac{\pi}{6}} ^{\frac{\pi}{3}}=\frac{\pi^2}{6}
